A Trip That Brings You Closer to Nature
The Oaks – Inverness
Serene & Off the Beaten Path
A Place Like No Other
Family Friendly
All members of your family are welcome; even the furry ones.  Please read our Property Policies for all updated information such as max capacities & pet fees.
Our Values & Traditions
We cherish our values and traditions by offering a serene retreat where guests can reconnect with nature. Our commitment is to provide a peaceful and rejuvenating experience, allowing visitors to escape the speed and noise of everyday life.
Why We Love This Place
Secluded
Walking Trails
Shaded By Nature
Horseback Riding
Natural Ponds
Flying Eagle Preserve
Near Crystal Rivers
Farm Animals
Surrounding Area
The Oaks – Inverness is your gateway to some of Florida’s finest attractions, all within a 45-minute drive. Enjoy a variety of outdoor adventures, from swimming in crystal-clear rivers and kayaking alongside manatees to exploring hidden caves and zip-lining through lush landscapes. Inverness also offers excellent fishing, thrilling airboat tours, and a diverse selection of dining experiences. Plus, just 20 minutes away, you’ll find all your essential needs, including grocery stores, pharmacies, and easy access to I-75.
Immerse yourself in the rich history of Inverness, FL. Originally known as Tompkinsville, the city was renamed by a Scottish land surveyor who found the area reminiscent of his homeland. In 1961, Elvis Presley brought a touch of Hollywood to our town while filming “Follow That Dream.” Today, Inverness proudly retains its historic charm with a vibrant downtown, a beautifully preserved courthouse, and annual festivals celebrating its unique heritage. Stay with us at The Oaks – Inverness and experience a perfect blend of adventure, history, and hospitality.
Sports and Recreational Opportunities
Less than a mile from the park is the Flying Eagle Preserve where there are 13 miles of trails for exploring.  The Flying Eagle Preserve is connected to the Withlacoochee River & Tsala Apopka Chain of Lakes. For Hunting Enthusiasts, the Preserve is closed to the General Public for a few days in January & permitted for hunting feral hogs.  See our Local Activities list for all other nearby sports & recreational opportunities.

A Family Operation
At The Oaks – Inverness
The property is family owned & operated.  As Florida Natives it is their mission to preserve Florida’s natural environment while creating spaces for others to enjoy.  A Family of Entrepreneurs dedicated to innovating business & property at The Oaks – Inverness.
